Individual Income Tax (Non Resident).information: Income Tax Rates for non residents

Higher Education Loan Program (HELP) Rep.information: Repayment amounts on HECS loans once income reaches a certain amount

Student Financial Supplement Scheme (SFS.information: Merged with HELP from FY2020 and beyond

Low Income Tax Offset.information: Offset against income tax for low income earners up to $66,667

Low Middle Income Tax Offset.information: Tax offset for low and middle income earners in the 2019 to 2022 income years.

Temporary budget repair levy.information: Additional 2% tax on high income earners for the 2017, 2016 and 2015FY

Medicare Levy Reduction.information: Reduction on the medicare levy depending on amount of famiily income

Medicare Levy Surchage.information: Additional Medicare Levy payable on high income earners with no private health insurance

Seniors and Pensioners Tax Offset.information: The tax offset reduces by $0.125 for every dollar your rebate income exceeds the relevant shading-out threshold amount. We round up the amount to the nearest whole dollar.

Mature Age Worker Tax Offset.information: It was introduced on 1 July 2004 and was available for 10 years before it was repealed on 1 July 2014. Non-refundable MAWTO credit of up to $500

Beneficiary Tax Offset.information: 15% of certain government based income calculated as an offset
